
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `bts` (Bluetoothctl) baraye modiriat dastgah-haaye Bluetooth az tarigh terminal estefade mishavad. Ba in dastoor mitoonid dastgah-ha ra peyda konid, vasl shavid, va etela'at ra darbare-ye aan-ha be dast aarid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `bluetoothctl` --> 💻 Baz kardan dastoor-e Bluetoothctl dar terminal.
    🔹 `bluetoothctl scan on` --> 📡 Shoru kardan jostojo baraye dastgah-haaye Bluetooth-e nazdik.
    🔹 `bluetoothctl pair [mac address]` --> 🔗 Vasl shodan be yek dastgah ba address MAC aan. (address MAC ra bayad jaye [mac address] benevisid)
    🔹 `bluetoothctl connect [mac address]` --> 📲 Etebasl mojadad be yek dastgah-e qablan vasl shode ba address MAC aan.
    🔹 `bluetoothctl disconnect [mac address]` --> ✂️ Ghot’ kardane etesal be yek dastgah ba address MAC aan.
    🔹 `bluetoothctl list` --> 📃 List kardan controller-haaye Bluetooth-e mojud.
    🔹 `bluetoothctl devices` --> 📱 List kardan dastgah-haaye vasl shode va payda shode.
    🔹 `bluetoothctl power on/off` --> 💡 Roshan ya khamush kardan Bluetooth.
    🔹 `bluetoothctl agent on/off` --> 🕵️‍  Enable/disable agent baraye handle connection-ha.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ bluetoothctl
    [bluetooth]# power on
    [bluetooth]# scan on
    [bluetooth]# devices

    🔹 Roshan kardan Bluetooth, shoru kardan scan, va list kardan dastgah-haaye payda shode.

    $ bluetoothctl
    [bluetooth]# connect XX:XX:XX:XX:XX:XX

    🔹 Vasl shodan be yek dastgah ba MAC address XX:XX:XX:XX:XX:XX.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ bluetoothctl scan on
    Discovery started
    [CHG] Controller AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF Discovering: yes
    [NEW] Device 00:11:22:33:44:55 Headphones

    🔹 Jostojo baraye dastgah-ha shoru shode va yek dastgah be name "Headphones" payda shode.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `bts` (Bluetoothctl) command is used to manage Bluetooth devices from the terminal. With this command, you can discover devices, connect to them, and obtain information about them.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `bluetoothctl` --> 💻 Open the Bluetoothctl command in the terminal.
    🔹 `bluetoothctl scan on` --> 📡 Start scanning for nearby Bluetooth devices.
    🔹 `bluetoothctl pair [mac address]` --> 🔗 Pair with a device using its MAC address. (Replace [mac address] with the actual MAC address).
    🔹 `bluetoothctl connect [mac address]` --> 📲 Reconnect to a previously paired device using its MAC address.
    🔹 `bluetoothctl disconnect [mac address]` --> ✂️ Disconnect from a device using its MAC address.
    🔹 `bluetoothctl list` --> 📃 List available Bluetooth controllers.
    🔹 `bluetoothctl devices` --> 📱 List paired and discovered devices.
    🔹 `bluetoothctl power on/off` --> 💡 Turn Bluetooth on or off.
    🔹 `bluetoothctl agent on/off` --> 🕵️‍  Enable/disable agent for handling connections.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ bluetoothctl
    [bluetooth]# power on
    [bluetooth]# scan on
    [bluetooth]# devices

    🔹 Turn on Bluetooth, start scanning, and list the discovered devices.

    $ bluetoothctl
    [bluetooth]# connect XX:XX:XX:XX:XX:XX

    🔹 Connect to a device with MAC address XX:XX:XX:XX:XX:XX.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ bluetoothctl scan on
    Discovery started
    [CHG] Controller AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF Discovering: yes
    [NEW] Device 00:11:22:33:44:55 Headphones

    🔹 Scanning for devices has started, and a device named "Headphones" has been found.

